Age Sex prediction

11/14/2023

correlation

  • Test set
r.dat = data.frame(combat.dat, nocombat.dat) %>%
  melt(.) %>%
  mutate(combat = substr(variable, 1,6), model = substr(variable,8,20)) %>%
  mutate(outcome = substr(model,1,3)) %>%
  mutate(cov = ifelse(substr(model,5,7)=='cov','W/ Cov','W/O Cov'))
## No id variables; using all as measure variables
ggplot(r.dat, aes(x = combat, y = value, fill = cov)) +
  facet_grid(.~ outcome) + 
  geom_split_violin(alpha = .4, trim = FALSE) +
  geom_boxplot(width = .2, alpha = .6, fatten = NULL, show.legend = FALSE) +
  stat_summary(fun.data = "mean_se", geom = "pointrange", show.legend = F, 
               position = position_dodge(.175)) +
  scale_x_discrete(name = "Combat Status", labels = c("Combat", "No Combat")) +
  scale_y_continuous(name = "Correlation between predicted and true values \n
                     in the test set") +
  #                   breaks = seq(200, 800, 100), 
  #                   limits = c(200, 800)) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Dark2", name = "Covarite Adjustment") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position='bottom',
        strip.text = element_text(size = 20))

library(emmeans)

r.dat %>% group_by(outcome, combat, cov) %>%
   summarise(mean=mean(value, na.rm=TRUE), se=sd(value, na.rm=TRUE)/sqrt(499))

r.dat = data.frame(combat.dat.train, nocombat.dat.train) %>%
  melt(.) %>%
  mutate(combat = substr(variable, 1,6), model = substr(variable,8,20)) %>%
  mutate(outcome = substr(model,1,3)) %>%
  mutate(cov = ifelse(substr(model,5,7)=='cov','W/ Cov','W/O Cov'))
## No id variables; using all as measure variables

  facet_grid(.~ outcome) + 
  geom_split_violin(alpha = .4, trim = FALSE) +
